"I was a stubborn maori boy who was too "PROUD" like many of us here who wouldnt open up to anything new. If I didn't agree then it was wrong.
All because I didn't know anything different.

Over the years Jillian has shown  me unconditional love through everything we have been through.

The most important thing was the way she connected with my family and sisters. She was keen to learn my culture and she has.

She changed my life for the better.

It took awhile for me to see it but she made me realize, even though my culture is everything, my family is everything my heritage is everything, it is only a part of me.

She made me realize that not only can you find happiness, but you can learn happiness. She took the time to learn about me so I took the time to learn about her.

I met her when she was 20 years of age, in another country when I was 19 years of age. So I was exposed to 20 years of memories, stories, and life.

It changed me but learning how to intertwine our lives has been the best experience.

Not only did I open up to the world but I learned how to love and connect with anyone on the planet.

I believe, she showed me how to be a man by being a woman." - Rawiri Nelson @the.rah #NewAgeGents
